, value, or meaning of nature as such, but there is a plethora of such factors evident in the evolved life forms of nature here on earth. This fact is especially evident in the day-to-day experiences, aspirations, and concerns of us evolutionarily-evolved human beings. Purpose, meaning, and value are therefore gifts of evolutionary nature, not of any supernatural or non-natural principle, presence, or power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 4aEnvironmental Studies : Ecology. 4aPhilosophy : Metaphysics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy of Science. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2023z978311149193640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143849398540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438493985423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438493985/original  a978-3-11-149193-6  SUNY Press eBook Package 2023b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles